</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 749<br> <font color=#333333>(8/22/02 7:39:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2924.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire and Talendor in camp...ouch. OMG a massacre and</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Had that wizzy nuked the human instead of agroing him, that would be engaging<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So let me get this straight.  If you're in a zone exping, and you're camping lets say, a 4 spawn of monsters.  You run over, hit one with an arrow, and all 4 aggro.  You mean to tell me, your group has no problem with someone else coming over, and taking the other 3 before you get back to your group because, you didn't, 'engage' them? <br>
<br>
No.  You'd bitch you were KS'd.  So would a ton of other people.  That's what happened here.  He was aggro'd, but someone else 'engaged' him.  You know, when RF was in SolB, the rule used to be, the second guild could not engage unless RF's aggro was clear, ie, no one is alive.<br>
<br>
What if I aggro, and it beats on me, but I don't attack? Does that count as engaging?<br>
<br>
And I think you proved Caladar's point when you pointed out that 'Why bother, all those other TW guilds don't listen'.  It doesn't matter if you've had other dealings, you still need to work out the compromise, per the rules.  Do I think Keuria deserved it? Yes.  I'm very glad that TFS got it.  I remember me and a couple guildies helping TFS camp another one for hours, only to have a guild pull BS with a GM.<br>
<br>
But I think a lot of people are being hypocritical.  If the situation was reversed, you'd come here flaming VD for being horrible people.  I've had good experiences with them, and absolutely, incredibly, i-hope-your-family-dies experiences with them.<br>
<br>
